	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">qbradq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Am I the only one that thinks the colors in Willow are a washed out nightmare? I mean seriously, there is hardly any contast at all.</div>
<br />I'm inclined to agree somewhat. A game should still look playable if all hues of $x1-$xC are transformed to $x7, or if the TV's "color" knob (saturation) is dialed down to zero.
<br />
<br />$01-$0C: halfway between $0F (black) and $00 (dark gray)
<br />$11-$1C: very close to $00
<br />$21-$2C: very close to $10 (light gray)
<br />$31-$3C: halfway between $10 and $30 (white)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
